#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:3
msgid "Part 2: Kinds of RL Algorithms"
msgstr "第二部分：強化學習 (RL) 演算法的種類"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:6
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:8
msgid ""
"Now that we've gone through the basics of RL terminology and notation, we"
" can cover a little bit of the richer material: the landscape of "
"algorithms in modern RL, and a description of the kinds of trade-offs "
"that go into algorithm design."
msgstr ""
"既然我們已經學習了 RL 術語和符號的基礎知識，我們可以涵蓋一些更豐富的內容：現代 "
"RL 演算法的全貌，以及演算法設計中所涉及的各種權衡的描述。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:11
msgid "A Taxonomy of RL Algorithms"
msgstr "RL 演算法的分類體系"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:16
msgid ""
"A non-exhaustive, but useful taxonomy of algorithms in modern RL. "
"`Citations below.`_"
msgstr ""
"現代 RL 演算法的一個非詳盡但實用的分類體系。`Citations below.`_"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:18
msgid ""
"We'll start this section with a disclaimer: it's really quite hard to "
"draw an accurate, all-encompassing taxonomy of algorithms in the modern "
"RL space, because the modularity of algorithms is not well-represented by"
" a tree structure. Also, to make something that fits on a page and is "
"reasonably digestible in an introduction essay, we have to omit quite a "
"bit of more advanced material (exploration, transfer learning, meta "
"learning, etc). That said, our goals here are"
msgstr ""
"我們先在本節開頭聲明：要為現代 RL 領域的演算法繪製一個準確、全面的分類體系確實"
"相當困難，因為演算法的模組化特性並不能很好地用樹狀結構來表示。此外，為了使內容"
"能在一頁內呈現，並在介紹性文章中保持合理的可讀性，我們不得不省略相當多的進階材"
"料（探索、遷移學習、元學習等）。話雖如此，我們在這裡的目標是"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:20
msgid ""
"to highlight the most foundational design choices in deep RL algorithms "
"about what to learn and how to learn it,"
msgstr ""
"突出深度 RL 演算法中關於學什麼以及如何學的最基礎設計選擇，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:21
msgid "to expose the trade-offs in those choices,"
msgstr "揭示這些選擇中的權衡，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:22
msgid ""
"and to place a few prominent modern algorithms into context with respect "
"to those choices."
msgstr "並將一些知名的現代演算法放在這些選擇的背景下加以定位。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:25
msgid "Model-Free vs Model-Based RL"
msgstr "無模型 (Model-Free) 與基於模型 (Model-Based) 的 RL"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:27
msgid ""
"One of the most important branching points in an RL algorithm is the "
"question of **whether the agent has access to (or learns) a model of the "
"environment**. By a model of the environment, we mean a function which "
"predicts state transitions and rewards."
msgstr ""
"RL 演算法中最重要的分支點之一是**代理人 (Agent) 是否能存取（或學習）環境的模型"
"**這個問題。所謂環境模型，我們指的是一個能預測狀態 (State) 轉移和獎勵 (Reward) "
"的函數。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:29
msgid ""
"The main upside to having a model is that **it allows the agent to plan**"
" by thinking ahead, seeing what would happen for a range of possible "
"choices, and explicitly deciding between its options. Agents can then "
"distill the results from planning ahead into a learned policy. A "
"particularly famous example of this approach is `AlphaZero`_. When this "
"works, it can result in a substantial improvement in sample efficiency "
"over methods that don't have a model."
msgstr ""
"擁有模型的主要優點是**它允許代理人進行規劃**——透過提前思考，看看一系列可能選擇"
"會發生什麼，並明確地在選項之間做出決定。然後代理人可以將規劃的結果提煉為學習到"
"的策略 (Policy)。這種方法的一個特別著名的例子是 `AlphaZero`_。當這種方法有效"
"時，它可以比沒有模型的方法在樣本效率 (Sample Efficiency) 上帶來顯著的提升。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:31
msgid ""
"The main downside is that **a ground-truth model of the environment is "
"usually not available to the agent.** If an agent wants to use a model in"
" this case, it has to learn the model purely from experience, which "
"creates several challenges. The biggest challenge is that bias in the "
"model can be exploited by the agent, resulting in an agent which performs"
" well with respect to the learned model, but behaves sub-optimally (or "
"super terribly) in the real environment. Model-learning is fundamentally "
"hard, so even intense effort---being willing to throw lots of time and "
"compute at it---can fail to pay off."
msgstr ""
"主要的缺點是**環境的真實模型通常對代理人不可用。** 如果代理人想在這種情況下使"
"用模型，它必須純粹從經驗中學習模型，這會產生幾個挑戰。最大的挑戰是模型中的偏差"
"可能被代理人利用，導致代理人在學習到的模型上表現良好，但在真實環境中表現欠佳"
"（或非常糟糕）。模型學習從根本上來說是困難的，所以即使付出巨大的努力——願意投入"
"大量的時間和算力——也可能無法獲得回報。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:33
msgid ""
"Algorithms which use a model are called **model-based** methods, and "
"those that don't are called **model-free**. While model-free methods "
"forego the potential gains in sample efficiency from using a model, they "
"tend to be easier to implement and tune. As of the time of writing this "
"introduction (September 2018), model-free methods are more popular and "
"have been more extensively developed and tested than model-based methods."
msgstr ""
"使用模型的演算法稱為**基於模型**的方法，不使用模型的稱為**無模型**的方法。雖然"
"無模型方法放棄了使用模型可能帶來的樣本效率提升，但它們通常更容易實作和調參。在"
"撰寫本介紹時（2018 年 9 月），無模型方法比基於模型的方法更受歡迎，也得到了更廣"
"泛的開發和測試。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:37
msgid "What to Learn"
msgstr "學什麼"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:39
msgid ""
"Another critical branching point in an RL algorithm is the question of "
"**what to learn.** The list of usual suspects includes"
msgstr ""
"RL 演算法中另一個關鍵的分支點是**學什麼**的問題。常見的候選項包括"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:41
msgid "policies, either stochastic or deterministic,"
msgstr "策略，隨機的或確定性的，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:42
msgid "action-value functions (Q-functions),"
msgstr "動作價值函數 (Action-Value Function)（Q 函數），"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:43
msgid "value functions,"
msgstr "價值函數 (Value Function)，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:44
msgid "and/or environment models."
msgstr "以及／或環境模型。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:49
msgid "What to Learn in Model-Free RL"
msgstr "在無模型 RL 中學什麼"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:51
msgid ""
"There are two main approaches to representing and training agents with "
"model-free RL:"
msgstr "在無模型 RL 中，有兩種主要方法來表示和訓練代理人："

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:53
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Policy Optimization.** Methods in this family represent a policy "
"explicitly as :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)`. They optimize the parameters "
":math:`\\theta` either directly by gradient ascent on the performance "
"objective :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})`,  or indirectly, by maximizing local "
"approximations of :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})`. This optimization is almost "
"always performed **on-policy**, which means that each update only uses "
"data collected while acting according to the most recent version of the "
"policy. Policy optimization also usually involves learning an "
"approximator :math:`V_{\\phi}(s)` for the on-policy value function "
":math:`V^{\\pi}(s)`, which gets used in figuring out how to update the "
"policy."
msgstr ""
"**策略優化 (Policy Optimization)。** 這一族方法將策略明確地表示為 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)`。它們透過對效能目標 :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})` 進行"
"梯度上升來直接最佳化參數 :math:`\\theta`，或者透過最大化 "
":math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})` 的局部近似來間接最佳化。這種最佳化幾乎總是以**同策略 "
"(On-Policy)** 的方式執行，這意味著每次更新只使用按照最新版本策略行動時收集的資"
"料。策略優化通常還涉及學習同策略價值函數 :math:`V^{\\pi}(s)` 的近似器 "
":math:`V_{\\phi}(s)`，用於確定如何更新策略。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:55
msgid "A couple of examples of policy optimization methods are:"
msgstr "策略優化方法的幾個例子是："

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:57
msgid ""
"`A2C / A3C`_, which performs gradient ascent to directly maximize "
"performance,"
msgstr "`A2C / A3C`_，透過梯度上升直接最大化效能，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:58
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"and `PPO`_, whose updates indirectly maximize performance, by instead "
"maximizing a *surrogate objective* function which gives a conservative "
"estimate for how much :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})` will change as a result "
"of the update."
msgstr ""
"以及 `PPO`_，其更新透過最大化一個*替代目標*函數來間接最大化效能，該替代目標函數"
"對 :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})` 因更新而產生的變化量給出保守估計。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:60
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Q-Learning.** Methods in this family learn an approximator "
":math:`Q_{\\theta}(s,a)` for the optimal action-value function, "
":math:`Q^*(s,a)`. Typically they use an objective function based on the "
"`Bellman equation`_. This optimization is almost always performed **off-"
"policy**, which means that each update can use data collected at any "
"point during training, regardless of how the agent was choosing to "
"explore the environment when the data was obtained. The corresponding "
"policy is obtained via the connection between :math:`Q^*` and "
":math:`\\pi^*`: the actions taken by the Q-learning agent are given by"
msgstr ""
"**Q 學習 (Q-Learning)。** 這一族方法學習最優動作價值函數 :math:`Q^*(s,a)` 的近"
"似器 :math:`Q_{\\theta}(s,a)`。它們通常使用基於 `Bellman equation`_ 的目標函"
"數。這種最佳化幾乎總是以**離策略 (Off-Policy)** 的方式執行，這意味著每次更新可"
"以使用訓練期間任何時間點收集的資料，而不管獲取資料時代理人是如何選擇探索環境"
"的。對應的策略透過 :math:`Q^*` 和 :math:`\\pi^*` 之間的關聯獲得：Q 學習代理人"
"採取的動作由以下公式給出"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:62
#, python-brace-format
msgid "a(s) = \\arg \\max_a Q_{\\theta}(s,a)."
msgstr "a(s) = \\arg \\max_a Q_{\\theta}(s,a)."

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:66
msgid "Examples of Q-learning methods include"
msgstr "Q 學習方法的例子包括"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:68
msgid "`DQN`_, a classic which substantially launched the field of deep RL,"
msgstr "`DQN`_，一個實質性地開創了深度 RL 領域的經典方法，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:69
msgid ""
"and `C51`_, a variant that learns a distribution over return whose "
"expectation is :math:`Q^*`."
msgstr ""
"以及 `C51`_，一個學習回報 (Return) 分佈的變體，其期望值為 :math:`Q^*`。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:71
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Trade-offs Between Policy Optimization and Q-Learning.** The primary "
"strength of policy optimization methods is that they are principled, in "
"the sense that *you directly optimize for the thing you want.* This tends"
" to make them stable and reliable. By contrast, Q-learning methods only "
"*indirectly* optimize for agent performance, by training "
":math:`Q_{\\theta}` to satisfy a self-consistency equation. There are "
"many failure modes for this kind of learning, so it tends to be less "
"stable. [1]_ But, Q-learning methods gain the advantage of being "
"substantially more sample efficient when they do work, because they can "
"reuse data more effectively than policy optimization techniques."
msgstr ""
"**策略優化與 Q 學習之間的權衡。** 策略優化方法的主要優勢在於它們是有原則的，因"
"為*你直接最佳化你想要的東西*。這使得它們趨向穩定和可靠。相比之下，Q 學習方法只"
"是透過訓練 :math:`Q_{\\theta}` 來滿足自洽方程式，從而*間接地*最佳化代理人效能。"
"這種學習方式有很多失敗模式，所以往往不太穩定。[1]_ 但是，Q 學習方法在有效時能"
"獲得顯著更高的樣本效率的優勢，因為它們可以比策略優化技術更有效地重用資料。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:73
msgid ""
"**Interpolating Between Policy Optimization and Q-Learning.** "
"Serendipitously, policy optimization and Q-learning are not incompatible "
"(and under some circumstances, it turns out, `equivalent`_), and there "
"exist a range of algorithms that live in between the two extremes. "
"Algorithms that live on this spectrum are able to carefully trade-off "
"between the strengths and weaknesses of either side. Examples include"
msgstr ""
"**在策略優化與 Q 學習之間插值。** 幸運的是，策略優化和 Q 學習並不是不相容的"
"（在某些情況下，事實上是 `equivalent`_ 的），而且存在一系列位於兩個極端之間的演"
"算法。位於這個頻譜上的演算法能夠在雙方的優缺點之間仔細權衡。例子包括"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:75
msgid ""
"`DDPG`_, an algorithm which concurrently learns a deterministic policy "
"and a Q-function by using each to improve the other,"
msgstr ""
"`DDPG`_，一種同時學習確定性策略和 Q 函數的演算法，透過讓它們相互改進，"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:76
msgid ""
"and `SAC`_, a variant which uses stochastic policies, entropy "
"regularization, and a few other tricks to stabilize learning and score "
"higher than DDPG on standard benchmarks."
msgstr ""
"以及 `SAC`_，一個使用隨機策略、熵正則化和一些其他技巧來穩定學習的變體，在標準"
"基準測試上得分高於 DDPG。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:80
msgid ""
"For more information about how and why Q-learning methods can fail, see "
"1) this classic paper by `Tsitsiklis and van Roy`_, 2) the (much more "
"recent) `review by Szepesvari`_ (in section 4.3.2), and 3) chapter 11 of "
"`Sutton and Barto`_, especially section 11.3 (on \"the deadly triad\" of "
"function approximation, bootstrapping, and off-policy data, together "
"causing instability in value-learning algorithms)."
msgstr ""
"關於 Q 學習方法如何以及為何會失敗的更多資訊，請參見 1) `Tsitsiklis and van "
"Roy`_ 的經典論文，2)（更近期的）`review by Szepesvari`_（第 4.3.2 節），以及 "
"3) `Sutton and Barto`_ 的第 11 章，特別是第 11.3 節（關於函數近似、自舉和離策略"
"資料的「致命三角」，它們共同導致價值學習演算法的不穩定性）。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:90
msgid "What to Learn in Model-Based RL"
msgstr "在基於模型的 RL 中學什麼"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:92
msgid ""
"Unlike model-free RL, there aren't a small number of easy-to-define "
"clusters of methods for model-based RL: there are many orthogonal ways of"
" using models. We'll give a few examples, but the list is far from "
"exhaustive. In each case, the model may either be given or learned."
msgstr ""
"與無模型 RL 不同，基於模型的 RL 沒有少數幾個容易定義的方法群組：使用模型有很多"
"正交的方式。我們將給出幾個例子，但這個列表遠非詳盡。在每種情況下，模型可以是預"
"先給定的或學習得到的。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:94
msgid ""
"**Background: Pure Planning.** The most basic approach *never* explicitly"
" represents the policy, and instead, uses pure planning techniques like "
"`model-predictive control`_ (MPC) to select actions. In MPC, each time "
"the agent observes the environment, it computes a plan which is optimal "
"with respect to the model, where the plan describes all actions to take "
"over some fixed window of time after the present. (Future rewards beyond "
"the horizon may be considered by the planning algorithm through the use "
"of a learned value function.) The agent then executes the first action of"
" the plan, and immediately discards the rest of it. It computes a new "
"plan each time it prepares to interact with the environment, to avoid "
"using an action from a plan with a shorter-than-desired planning horizon."
msgstr ""
"**背景：純規劃。** 最基本的方法*從不*明確地表示策略，而是使用純規劃技術，如 "
"`model-predictive control`_（MPC，模型預測控制）來選擇動作 (Action)。在 MPC "
"中，每當代理人觀測環境時，它會計算一個相對於模型最優的計劃，該計劃描述了從當前"
"時刻起在某個固定時間窗口內要採取的所有動作。（超出時間範圍的未來獎勵可以透過使"
"用學習到的價值函數被規劃演算法考慮。）然後代理人執行計劃的第一個動作，並立即丟"
"棄其餘部分。它每次準備與環境互動時都會計算一個新的計劃，以避免使用來自規劃時間"
"範圍不夠長的計劃中的動作。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:96
msgid ""
"The `MBMF`_ work explores MPC with learned environment models on some "
"standard benchmark tasks for deep RL."
msgstr ""
"`MBMF`_ 的工作在一些深度 RL 的標準基準任務上探索了使用學習到的環境模型的 MPC。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:98
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Expert Iteration.** A straightforward follow-on to pure planning "
"involves using and learning an explicit representation of the policy, "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)`. The agent uses a planning algorithm (like "
"Monte Carlo Tree Search) in the model, generating candidate actions for "
"the plan by sampling from its current policy. The planning algorithm "
"produces an action which is better than what the policy alone would have "
"produced, hence it is an \"expert\" relative to the policy. The policy is"
" afterwards updated to produce an action more like the planning "
"algorithm's output."
msgstr ""
"**專家迭代。** 純規劃的一個直接後續發展涉及使用和學習策略的明確表示 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)`。代理人在模型中使用規劃演算法（如蒙特卡洛樹搜尋），"
"透過從當前策略中抽樣來生成計劃的候選動作。規劃演算法產生的動作比僅靠策略產生的"
"動作更好，因此它相對於策略而言是一個「專家」。之後策略會被更新，以產生更接近規"
"劃演算法輸出的動作。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:100
msgid ""
"The `ExIt`_ algorithm uses this approach to train deep neural networks to"
" play Hex."
msgstr "`ExIt`_ 演算法使用這種方法訓練深度神經網路來玩 Hex 遊戲。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:101
msgid "`AlphaZero`_ is another example of this approach."
msgstr "`AlphaZero`_ 是這種方法的另一個例子。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:103
msgid ""
"**Data Augmentation for Model-Free Methods.** Use a model-free RL "
"algorithm to train a policy or Q-function, but either 1) augment real "
"experiences with fictitious ones in updating the agent, or 2) use *only* "
"fictitous experience for updating the agent."
msgstr ""
"**無模型方法的資料增強。** 使用無模型 RL 演算法來訓練策略或 Q 函數，但 1) 在更"
"新代理人時用虛構的經驗來增強真實經驗，或 2) *僅*使用虛構經驗來更新代理人。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:105
msgid ""
"See `MBVE`_ for an example of augmenting real experiences with fictitious"
" ones."
msgstr "請參見 `MBVE`_ 作為用虛構經驗增強真實經驗的例子。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:106
msgid ""
"See `World Models`_ for an example of using purely fictitious experience "
"to train the agent, which they call \"training in the dream.\""
msgstr ""
"請參見 `World Models`_ 作為使用純虛構經驗訓練代理人的例子，他們稱之為「在夢中"
"訓練」。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:108
msgid ""
"**Embedding Planning Loops into Policies.** Another approach embeds the "
"planning procedure directly into a policy as a subroutine---so that "
"complete plans become side information for the policy---while training "
"the output of the policy with any standard model-free algorithm. The key "
"concept is that in this framework, the policy can learn to choose how and"
" when to use the plans. This makes model bias less of a problem, because "
"if the model is bad for planning in some states, the policy can simply "
"learn to ignore it."
msgstr ""
"**將規劃迴圈嵌入策略。** 另一種方法是將規劃程序直接嵌入策略中作為子程序——使完整"
"的計劃成為策略的附加資訊——同時使用任何標準的無模型演算法來訓練策略的輸出。關鍵"
"概念是在這個框架中，策略可以學習如何以及何時使用計劃。這使得模型偏差不再是那麼"
"大的問題，因為如果模型在某些狀態下不適合規劃，策略可以簡單地學習忽略它。"

#: ../../spinningup/rl_intro2.rst:110
msgid ""
"See `I2A`_ for an example of agents being endowed with this style of "
"imagination."
msgstr "請參見 `I2A`_ 作為賦予代理人這種想像力風格的例子。"

